{
  "answer": "**The Āṅgirasa Smṛti in this corpus does not contain a specific verse prescribing prayāścitta (expiation) for forgetting the Gāyatrī mantra.** \n\nThe text discusses prayāścitta extensively, often recommending recitation of the Gāyatrī or Vyāhṛtis as a general expiation (e.g., 10,000 recitations for neglecting a death anniversary[^1]; oblations with Vyāhṛti and Gāyatrī in a marriage-related rite[^2]). However, no verse addresses forgetting the Gāyatrī specifically. The corpus covers 37 works; this topic may appear elsewhere (e.g., other Smṛtis), but not here.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Āṅgirasa Smṛti, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-b061ae).\n[^2]: Āṅgirasa Smṛti, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-9cc063).\n[^3]: Āṅgirasa Smṛti, Chapter 1, [full chapter](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/).",
